headline: Why Analysts Are Rethinking CarMax as Changing Results Shift the Story
summary: CarMax's consensus analyst price target has recently dropped from $81.44 to $76.93. This reflects a shift in sentiment following a challenging second quarter. Recent underperformance across several key metrics and increased uncertainty around the company's strategic outlook have prompted many analysts to adopt a more cautious view.
